  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The use of eccentric resistance training as management of Achilles tendinopathy is
      widespread. The investigators have recently demonstrated that heavy slow resistance training
      was superior in the management of patellar tendinopathy.

      Hypothesis: heavy slow resistance training is more effective than eccentric resistance
      training in the clinical management of Achilles tendinopathy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
